The replaceAll() method replaces each substring that matches the regex(regular expression) of the string with the specified text.

-----
Syntax of replaceAll():  string.replaceAll(String regex, String replacement)

-----
Example: Java String replaceAll()

class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    String str1 = "aabbaaac";
    String str2 = "Learn223Java55@";

    String regex = "\\d+";    // regex for sequence of digits
    
    System.out.println(str1.replaceAll("aa", "zz"));    // all occurrences of "aa" is replaceAll with "zz"

    System.out.println(str2.replaceAll(regex, " "));    // replace a digit or sequence of digits with a whitespace
  }
}

o/p:
zzbbzzac
Learn Java @


